Wizkid’s fourth studio album ‘Made In Lagos,’ has been certified Silver in the United Kingdom by the BPI, the UK record labels association. ‘Made In Lagos’ was certified Silver after the album sold a little over 60,000 units in the United Kingdom and environs. The certification was announced on the official Twitter handle of the Brit Awards. The Tweets reads: ‘Made In Lagos’, the album by Wizkid, is now #BRITcertified Silver.”   Obi Cubana offers Lagos hawker university scholarship,…     Uzodinma appoints Cubana Chief Priest Special Adviser     Ex- BBNaija’s Nini Singh shows off six cars worth N55m   - Advertisement - Currently, singles are awarded Platinum status when, based on Official Charts Company data, they achieve 600,000 units, Gold for 400,000 units and Silver for 200,000 units. For albums, 300,000 units are required to achieve Platinum certification, 100,000 for Gold and 60,000 for Silver. The UK record labels association the BPI administers and certifies the iconic BRIT Certified Platinum, Gold, and Silver Awards Programme. This recognises and celebrates the commercial success of music recordings and videos released in the UK.